entries.title: Intel Shares Drop After Disappointing Earnings
entries.description: The chip maker reported a loss in the fourth quarter as shifting demand and a battle for market share darkens its outlook in the months ahead.

entries.title: Salesforce Names Three Directors, Braces for Proxy Fight
entries.description: The appointments follow activist investor Elliott Management’s investment in the business-software provider.

entries.title: Guess Who's Using Your Netflix Account? You Might Be Surprised.
entries.description: Maybe you forgot to log out at a rental, or your ex’s sister is still enjoying ‘The Crown.’ A new tool on the streaming service shows where and when your account has been used—and lets you boot off the moochers.

entries.title: Google Tries to Catch Up to Rivals Like  OpenAI as They Release Viral Apps
entries.description: The tech giant’s invention led to recent breakthroughs in AI chatbots and image programs now being popularized by competitors.

entries.title: Meta Embraces AI as Facebook, Instagram Help Drive a Rebound
entries.description: After the roughest year in its history, Facebook’s parent company is starting to bounce back. Users are watching its short-form videos, ad-targeting is improving and the social-media company is well down the road to recovering from the impact of privacy changes imposed by Apple.

entries.title: People Can't Stop 'Spotify Snooping' on Friends, Exes and Crushes
entries.description: The practice is a sneaky way to check how people are feeling—without having to interact with them.

entries.title: Tesla Has Become One of the Hottest Stock-Option Trades on Wall Street
entries.description: Traders have spent $700 billion on options tied to the electric-vehicle maker over the past 13 months.

entries.title: Israel's Tech Sector Opposes Judicial-Overhaul Plan
entries.description: Tech firms have said the government’s proposed changes to the top court are spooking investors worried about economic stability, the independence of the courts and a right-wing legislative agenda.
